Connections in Universitat Pompeu Fabra #Barcelona #Spain, please welcome Ashwin S! A is currently pursuing MSc at UPF. A was a #ResearchAssociate with us from 2021-2022; “feedback [from the group] that helped me get to a common ground across collaborators from different backgrounds… this remains one of the most invaluable skills I’ve developed in interdisciplinary research” writes A, in their blogpost on “Reflections & Lessons from a Year at Precog”. Read more: https://precog.iiit.ac.in/blog/2023/09/21/reflections-lessons-from-a-year-at-precog/ A worked in #BigData #ICT4D on improving adoption rates of farming practices with Digital Green and uncovering #DarkPatterns and #Fraud on Google Play. A’s work was published at #ACM #ICTD, #Hypertext, and covered by the Montreal AI Ethics Institute. A also enjoys running and playing guitar ! If you are around, feel free to say hi / connect with A. #PrecogsRock #ProudAdvisor #ProfGiri Read A’s work: Diagnosing Data to Improve Adoption Rates @ ICTD ‘22: https://dl.acm.org/doi/abs/10.1145/3572334.3572400 Dark Patterns & Fraud on Google Play @ Hypertext ‘22, AI Ethics Brief: https://dl.acm.org/doi/abs/10.1145/3511095.3536368, https://montrealethics.ai/labor-and-fraud-on-the-google-play-store-the-case-of-install-incentivizing-apps/
